main event: A small, very brilliant object dived vertically from a very high altitude at tremendous speed over the Philadelphia Airport in Pennsylvania.
interesting points: The object leveled off and then disappeared to the south.
There were two visual sightings of the object from the ground by a witness.
The object was estimated to be over the North Philadelphia Airport, observed from an address south two miles northwest of the airport.
The speed of the object was estimated to be very high, being in the same area at the same time.
The weather conditions were CAVU (ceiling and visibility unlimited) with winds at 44,020 feet estimated at 233/73.
result: Insufficient information, but possibly a jet aircraft or unidentified in the area.
